external_knowledge:
- "blossoms named with 'example'" refers to products whose names contain the word "example";
- "eager gardeners" refers to users who have left comments;
- "guidebook" refers to user manuals.

- 'blossoms' refers to products;
- 'garden of innovation' refers to the product development and testing environment;
- 'testing phase of their growth cycle' refers to the 'Testing' phase in the product lifecycle;
- 'spoken about more than once' refers to having more than one comment;
- 'gardeners' refers to users or commenters;
- 'between the dawn of 2020 and the twilight of 2021' refers to the date range from January 1, 2020, to December 31, 2021.

- "Blooms" and "garden" are metaphors for products and the product development process, respectively;
- "Seasoned gardener" refers to the product manager with ID 2;
- "Phases of growth" represent the lifecycle phases of the products;
- "Average time spent in each phase" is calculated using the start and end dates of the lifecycle phases.

- The total duration of lifecycle phases is calculated in days;
- Only products with at least one associated document are considered;
- The results are ordered by the total duration in descending order.

sql:
SELECT step_name, step_status
FROM workflow_steps
WHERE step_status = 'pending';

SELECT JULIANDAY(release_date) AS julian_release_date
FROM product_versions
WHERE version_id = 0;

